

üìò Project Log: Mobile IDs ‚Äî Device Data Collector via ADB

üß© Project Goal

To build a Mobile IDs system that can connect to multiple Android devices (real or virtual), collect kernel-level and system-level performance data, and store it for further analysis ‚Äî forming the foundation for a mobile analytics or monitoring framework.


---

‚öô Setup Progress

‚úÖ 1. ADB (Android Debug Bridge) Installation

Installed ADB platform tools manually (without Android Studio).

Extracted tools to:

C:\platform-tools

Verified ADB installation using:

adb version
adb devices

Confirmed that the phone connects via USB debugging and later through Wi-Fi (hotspot connection).



---

‚úÖ 2. Device Connectivity Testing

Verified connection using:

adb devices

Start developer mode in mobile to access adb

Connected over both:

USB

Wi-Fi (via hotspot) using IP connection
Example:

adb tcpip 5555
adb connect 192.168.x.x:5555




---

‚ö† 3. IP Retrieval Issue

Discovered that usb0 and rndis0 interfaces do not exist on newer phones.

Found actual network interface as:

swlan0 (IP: 192.168.23.28)

Confirmed hotspot-based ADB connection possible.



---

üß† 4. Batch Script for Automated Data Collection
File:windows.bat

Purpose:
> To automatically connect device over hotspot and manage connection 

File: collect_device.bat

Purpose:

> To automatically collect hardware, OS, and performance metrics from any connected Android phone and save them in a timestamped folder.



Main operations:

Detects first available ADB device.

Collects:

System properties ‚Üí getprop.txt

CPU info ‚Üí proc_cpuinfo.txt

Memory info ‚Üí proc_meminfo.txt

Dumpsys memory report ‚Üí dumpsys_meminfo.txt

Recent logs ‚Üí logcat.txt

Screenshot ‚Üí screen.png

Kernel logs (if accessible) ‚Üí dmesg.txt



Output structure:

adb_collect_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS/
‚îÇ
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ getprop.txt
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ proc_cpuinfo.txt
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ proc_meminfo.txt
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dumpsys_meminfo.txt
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ logcat.txt
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dmesg.txt
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ dmesg_err.txt (if dmesg blocked)
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ screen.png


---

üö´ 5. dmesg Access Restriction

Command:

adb shell dmesg

‚Üí returned Permission denied on non-rooted device.

Reason:

Modern Android (8+) blocks kernel ring buffer access for security.


Alternatives used/planned:

adb bugreport bugreport.zip ‚Üí for kernel traces.

/proc/ and dumpsys ‚Üí for safe stats.

adb logcat -b kernel ‚Üí sometimes works on OEM builds.




---

üß© 6. Real-time Logs Exploration

Used:

adb logcat

‚Üí entered continuous live log stream.

Exited safely using: Ctrl + C

Learned alternate modes:

Action	Command

Dump once & exit	adb logcat -d
Last 200 lines	adb logcat -t 200
Clear logs	adb logcat -c




